Barrett Company, Libelant-Appellant, v. Steam Tug MARY J. KENNEDY, Her Engines, etc.; Elizabeth Company, Claimant-Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 19,1926.) No. 262. Maeklin, Brown & Van Wyek, of New York City (Horace L. Cheyney, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Foley & Martin and William J. Martin, all of New York City, for appellee.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (11 F.[2d] 623) affirmed, with costs.
